  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Fri, 23 Jul. 2021&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF ACADEMIC SERVICES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ASSISTANT DIRECTOR, STUDENT RECORDS AND EXAMINATIONS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: IRC 956&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;(i)&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;To manage student academic records including grades collection, processing and reporting, C/GPA calculations, enrolment verifications, graduation checking, transcript production, and certificate production; (ii) develop and implement effective and efficient systems for collecting, processing, storage, retrieval, release, analysis, security and integrity of students records and information; (iii) develops and implements effective policies and procedures; (iv) coordinates administration of academic appeals; (v) manages information service; (vi) effectively coordinate with academic and service units and manage system changes, enhancements and interfaces with other systems; (vii) promotes the use of electronic systems and online services; data analysis and statistical reporting; (viii) effective examination scheduling including the security and integrity of examination papers; (ix) manages internal and external examinations service; (x) leads automation efforts in unit and support campus-wide initiatives; (xi) promotes and implements academic honesty policies and enforce official decisions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; (i)&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;A minimum of a Bachelor’s degree in any discipline. (ii) A minimum of five years post-Bachelor’s degree work experience in academic and/or student academic services. (iii) Work experience in academic assessment; examination administration services; integrated electronic student information systems; relational&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; databases and student records management system such as ERP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;; Web-enabled services. (iv) Knowledge of relevant regulations such as academic and examinations regulations, and quality standards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; include: planning, analytical, problem-solving, interpersonal and communication skills; team leadership; absolute integrity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;: The University offers competitive salary commensurate with experience and qualifications. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to Apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;: Letters of applications stating qualifications, experience and other relevant information (including telephone and email) as well as  current CV’s, certified true copies of educational certificates, transcripts, three reference letters and names of three referees should be addressed to: &lt;strong&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Appointments and Administration, University of Botswana, Private Bag 0022, Gaborone; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;; Telephone: (+267) 355 2048/ 2040: Email: Ramahobok@ub.ac.bw  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to (i) &lt;strong&gt;Quote the Vacancy Number and Position applied for &lt;/strong&gt;and (ii) &lt;strong&gt;submit their references directly to the above address&lt;/strong&gt;, before the stipulated closing date. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted at &lt;strong&gt;Block 108 Office No 205 (108/205). &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB: Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;CLOSING DATE: 23RD JULY 2021&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
